The following Python code is supposed to find all prime numbers up to N using the Sieve of Eratosthenes, but it produces wrong results for N=10.

Code:
```python
def sieve(n):
    primes = [True] * n
    primes[0] = primes[1] = False
    for i in range(2, n):
        if primes[i]:
            for j in range(i*2, n, i):
                primes[j] = False
    return [i for i, p in enumerate(primes) if p]
```

